# Mirror the publish scrub (build_public_tree.py) so an image built from ANY context
# — even the private source tree — can never bake in the internal/coupled files.
# Belt-and-suspenders: the public repo already excludes these; this keeps the image
# clean regardless of build context.
deponent/attest.py
tests/test_attest.py
deponent/adapters/provenant_rs.py
PUBLISH_MANIFEST.md
PUBLISH_CHECKLIST.md
PLAN.md
README_SDK.md
API_SURFACE.md
docs/RUST_ADAPTER_SPEC.md
scripts/build_public_tree.py
scripts/verify_wheel.py
ANNOUNCEMENTS.md

# build noise — use **/ so NESTED dirs are matched too (a bare `__pycache__/` only
# matches root level, which let a compiled deponent/__pycache__/attest.*.pyc leak in).
.git
.venv
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/attest*                 # belt: no attest source OR bytecode, at any depth
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
runs/
.DS_Store
